---
source: crates/data-dict/tests/validate_spec.rs
---
# expected: S06
# `cardinality: many-to-one` requires the right-side join column to be
# `primary_key` or `unique`. Here `account.account_id` is `required` but
# neither unique nor PK. No `foreign_key` constraints are set so S01 does
# not fire alongside this one.

$version: "0.1.0"

tables:
  - name: transaction
    columns:
      - name: id
        type: number(id)
        constraints: [primary_key]
        examples: [1, 2]
      - name: account_id
        type: number(id)
        constraints: [required]
        examples: [1, 2]

  - name: account
    columns:
      - name: account_id
        type: number(id)
        constraints: [required]
        examples: [1, 2]

relationships:
  - join: transaction.account_id = account.account_id
    cardinality: many-to-one
────────────────────────────────────────
error[S06]: A `many-to-one` join must have a `primary_key` or `unique` column on its right ("one") side.
  --> spec/s06-cardinality-mismatch.yaml:30:18
   |
LL |   - join: transaction.account_id = account.account_id
LL |     cardinality: many-to-one
   |                  ^^^^^^^^^^^ the right-side join column on `account` is not marked `primary_key` or `unique`
